			<ns0:name>b...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/105821748722532785568/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">untrusted x86-64 code uses __tls_get_addr which performs a syscall.  this makes the syscall path extremely hot in code that uses TLS frequently.

until the TC makes the compiler try to reduce multiple invocations to __tls_get_addr and strength reduce it out of loops etc, we should simultaneously modify the service runtime so that the syscall is cheaper.

this is related to http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=221 but that is more TC-side.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-10-12T16:55:42.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-10-05T20:33:37.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
